text: Benton County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 25,575. The county seat is Vinton. The county is named for Thomas Hart Benton, a U.S. Senator from Missouri. Benton County was founded on December 21, 1837. == References == Category:1837 establishments in Wisconsin Territory Category:Iowa counties
title: Benton County, Iowa
